summary: I've watched Aggretsuko and I can safely say that I am a fan of the show now! I'm looking foward to Season 2 this year!
body:
I’ve watched Aggretsuko and I can safely say that I am a fan of the show now! I’m looking foward to Season 2 this year!

My favorite characters are Retsuko (the one I relate to the most), Fenneko (my spirit animal), Tsunoda (I love her and hate her at the same time), and Haida (the precious hyena boy)!

summary: The American voice actress for Tsunoda (in the US dub of the Netflix anime Aggretsuko) actually ships Fenneko and Tsunoda...
body:
The American voice actress for Tsunoda (in the US dub of the Netflix anime Aggretsuko) actually ships Fenneko and Tsunoda together as confirmed by a reply she gave to a piece of fanart between the two female characters! (But this does NOT however, confirm that the ship to be canonical. It’s just her own opinion that she formed towards it.)

Link to the original post and GK’s response: https://mobile.twitter.com/gkbowes/status/993067632550002693

title: The Wedding Part 1: The Invites
body:
Retsuko: Okay! We got the families settled, Fenneko found a good place for the wedding, now all we have to do is get invitations ready!

Haida: Alrighty…who do we invite? Aside from, obviously, family and friends.

Retsuko: ……well, that’s a problem, who do we classify as a friend?

Haida: I…..hmm. Well, Fenneko, obviously.

Retsuko: Of course. Gori and Washimi are friends of mine.

Haida: Okay, they’re in.

Retsuko: …um….Tsunoda?

Haida: …..I mean…if you want. I dunno, I don’t think much about her.

Retsuko: Yeah, but she’s helped me out in a few places, and it would feel weird to have a gathering like that without her…plus, we KNOW Fenneko and her are going out.

Haida: Eh, true. Erm…Ookami?

Retsuko: ….I kinda forgot he existed, honestly.

Haida: Same. But, ya know. He’s always nice to us.

Retsuko: I suppose. How about Resasuke?

Haida: …

Retsuko: …….Haida? Are you still bitter over what happened?

Haida: Firstly, was never bitter about it.

Retsuko: Suuuure.

Haida: Second….I dunno, that sounds a little weird, doesn’t it? Your ex attending your wedding? I mean, I have nothing against the guy, but still. :/

Retsuko: That’s true. But…I dunno, I know he means well. He’s a good guy. It just didn’t work out.

Haida: Well….oh, alright. :)

Retsuko: Mhm! Ton-

Both: Nope.

Haida: Komi-

Both: NOPE.

Retsuko: Tsub-

Both: NOPE.

Retsuko: Oh! Puko! Gotta get her in.

Haida: Okay….Kabae?

Retsuko: ……….eh, sure.

Haida: Okay. Now we got those, and our folks….hmm.

Retsuko: …something wrong?

Haida: …ah, it’s nothing. Just…for some reason, the fact your brother doesn’t like me is kinda bugging me.

Retsuko: Oh, Ryuu? Ah, he’s just a teen. He’ll get over it soon enough. He used to worship my dad from the ground he walked on. So, hopefully, with dad warming up, he’ll do the same.

Haida: He literally tried to attack me again as we were leaving.

Retsuko: …baby steps, Haida.

Haida: Does 16 count as “baby”?

*the next day, the two begin sending out the invitations*

Puko: Bitchin’! Awesome, Retsuko! I’ll try to make it there!

Kabae: EEEEEEEEE! Oh, boy, I can’t wait! I always knew you two would make it!

Ookami: Oh. Cool. Yeah, I could make it, probably.

Resasuke: …………could I bring a plant?

Haida: ….um….sure?

Resasuke: Great. See you then.

Washimi: Absolutely. It would be an honor to attend.

Gori: WOO-HOO! You go, girl! Of course I can make it there!

*and finally…*

Tsunoda: …an invite to your wedding, huh?

Retsuko: Y-yeah! You know, if you WANT to go…

Tsunoda: …mhmhm! You two are silly! I don’t need an invite, *starts walking away* I’m already helping with it!

Retsuko: …wait, you’re helping?

Fenneko: *pops in* Oh, I forgot to mention, Tsunoda effectively forced herself into the wedding party committee.

Haida: …she what?!

Fenneko: ……………surprise! :3
